CatDescriptText: Miss Joyce Gilbert, 222 Wykes Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "What do you think is wrong with the Pittsburgh Pirates? Do you think that they are using their best ball players at all times?" answer reads: "Yes, I do."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Joyce Gilbert wearing dark dress with covered buttons running down sleeves, jeweled brooch, and sunglasses, standing in front light colored pillar across from Buhl Building with sign for "Fashion hosiery shops...", corner of Fifth Avenue and Market Street, Downtown
